What does this program print?

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <vector>

int main()
{
    std::vector<int> v { 10, 20, 30 };
    for (int i = static_cast<int>(v.size()) - 1; i >= 0; --i)
        std::cout << v[i] << ' ';
    std::cout << '\n';
}
```

This program is intended to print the elements of `v` in reverse, but it loops forever. Why?

